The paper discusses the application of deep reinforcement learning (DRL) to solve nonlinear differential equations, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE). The use of DRL also involves control engineering (cs.CE) and reinforcement learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the embedding of physical laws into the DRL network, which relates to systems and control (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
